law.text:
A local management board may be composed of:
public and private community representatives who share the responsibility for implementing a community-based, interagency, family-focused service delivery system for children, youth, and families;
a senior representative or department head of the:
local health department;
local office of the Department of Juvenile Services;
core service agency;
local school system; and
local department of social services;
family members or family advocates; and
youth or youth advocates.
